{{sbarinfo|invulnerable, <image-on>, <image-off>, <x>, <y> [, {center{{!}}centerbottom}]}}
{{sbarinfo|[[LOCKDEFS|keyslot]] <#> [&& <#>, <image0>, <image1>], <image2>, <image3>, <x>, <y> [, {center{{!}}centerbottom}]}}
{{sbarinfo|[[Classes:BasicArmor|armortype]] <armor1> [&& <armor2>, <image0>, <image1>], <image2>, <image3>, <x>, <y> [, {center{{!}}centerbottom}]}} 
{{sbarinfo|<[[Classes:Inventory|inventory_item]]> [&& <inventory_item>, <image0>, <image1>], <image2>, <image3>, <x>, <y> [, {center{{!}}centerbottom}]}}
{{sbarinfo|weaponslot <#> [&& <#>, <image0>, <image1>], <image2>, <image3>, <x>, <y> [, {center{{!}}centerbottom}]}}
Draws a particular image if the player fills a given condition, such as having a particular item. The item may be any sub-class of Inventory. If the player is carrying the item then {{c|image3}} is drawn, else {{c|image2}} is drawn.  

If a second item is specified with the {{c|&&}} operator, an additional two images are required. In that case, {{c|image0}} is drawn if the player is holding none of the items, {{c|image1}} if the player is holding {{c|item1}}, {{c|image2}} if the player is holding just {{c|item2}}, and {{c|image3}} if the player is holding both.

Comparison operators can be used to check for a specific value of an item or armor.
